Course outline

Homework

There will be six homework assignments through the semester.

  • 40% of final grade
  • Can work in groups, but turn in individual work
  • No late homework
  • Any indication of copying will result into a zero score

Homeworks of this class are real fun. If you dont struggle with the HW you will not learn real. They are designed to give you the opportunity to learn through experience.

Project Description

No exam! Submit a group project (60% of final grade).

  • Form group by next week
  • Each group consists of 4-5 students
  • Submit real data project
    • Feb 28: proposal due
    • March 31: midterm report due
    • May 11: final report due
    • May 11: project presentation

Why project?

  • Most of your interview questions will be on the project
  • Get your future career under shape (Fatten your CV)
  • The reality teaches in many ways that nobody can
  • Be confident
  • Learn how to collaborate

How does a project die?

How do you think a project dies after you have submitted and got grades on it?

  • Throw it out and dont look back again
  • Not reproducible and lazy to do it again
  • Sit and see what others did on the group and you dont have a feel for it
  • No future plan with it
  • Fear competition
  • Dont want to participate
    • Data expo

Grading

Data Science lab

The data science lab location: DSC 243

  • Data science tools are available
  • Can get access to high performance computing (HCC)
  • Lab user manual
  • You can prepare your own machine (like the lab) for small task
  • How to prepare a data science lab

Install R and RStudio

The data science lab has both R and RStudio installed.

  • Get R from http://cran.r-project.org/
  • Install a typesetting software latex or Miktex from http://miktex.org/download
    for MAC user it would be MacTex
  • Get RStudio desktop version from http://www.rstudio.com/
  • RStudio provides convenient environment.

Please make sure you install them in the sequence mentioned above.

Benefit from this course

  • Tools and technics of data science
  • How to create data product
  • Reproducible analysis of data
  • Your own data analysis project
  • Contribute to a data driven society
  • Not scared of data
  • Not shy of data

Are you data literate?

Why needs data literacy?

  • Industries
    • business managements
    • optimizing resource allocation and profit
    • Reliability of products and predictions
  • Academics
    • Researchers running experiments producing data
    • Post docs working day and night to help researchers
    • PhD Students who are working on their dissertations

Data Scientists are in demand

  • Many industries feel the need
    • Healthcare industries are opening new positions
    • Methodist Healthcare System alone hired 6 students from our class in 2017.
  • Omaha has companies employing data scientists from our program
    • TDAmeritrade
    • First National Bank
    • OPPD
    • Union Pacific
    • and more
